  "narration": "A bridge unrolls itself like a scroll read aloud by an engineer with a poet’s day job. Planks are engraved with numbers, not sequential but conditional: this plank is number Seven if you stepped kindly on Five; this plank is number Three if your left foot apologized to your right for hurrying. Handrails bloom only when two hands ask politely at the same moment. A diagram carved into the near post shows, with loving clarity, how to cross without making the bridge feel taken for granted. A chorus of lanterns waits to grade your posture and offer extra credit for good jokes that admit fear without worshiping it. Beneath, a dry channel full of polite pebbles makes a sound like old typewriters, the keys willing to record but unwilling to lie.",
